fields.name: Duval Street
fields.itinerary_description: Shopping and lunch at Half Shell Raw Bar on Duval Street

fields.name: Watch the Sunset
fields.itinerary_description: Enjoy the sunset views from Mallory Square.  Hopefully, we'll see some live performers too!

fields.name: Dinner
fields.itinerary_description: Dinner at Conch Republic Seafood Company: Located in the Historic Seaport area of Key West, this restaurant has indoor and outdoor seating with views of the harbor. The menu features a variety of fresh seafood dishes and Key West specialties like conch fritters and key lime pie.

fields.name: Watch the Sunset
fields.itinerary_description: Enjoy the sunset views from Mallory Square.  Hopefully, we'll see some live performers too!

fields.name: Breakfast at Blue Heaven
fields.itinerary_description: Enjoy breakfast at Blue Heaven, a popular Key West restaurant known for its outdoor seating and laid-back atmosphere. Try the banana pancakes or the lobster benedict!

fields.name: Explore Old Town
fields.itinerary_description: Take a walk through Old Town Key West, known for its historic architecture and charming streets. Stop by the Ernest Hemingway Home and Museum to see where the famous writer lived and wrote some of his most famous works.

fields.name: Lunch at El Meson de Pepe
fields.itinerary_description: Enjoy a delicious Cuban lunch at El Meson de Pepe, located in the heart of Mallory Square. Try the ropa vieja or the Cuban sandwich!

fields.name: Beach Time
fields.itinerary_description: Spend the afternoon relaxing on the beach at Smathers Beach. Take a swim, soak up the sun, and enjoy the beautiful views of the ocean.

fields.name: Sunset Sail
fields.itinerary_description: Take a sunset sail on a catamaran and enjoy the beautiful views of the sunset over the water. Drinks and snacks will be provided.

fields.name: Louie's Backyard
fields.itinerary_description: Enjoy dinner at Louie's Backyard, a fine-dining restaurant located on the ocean with beautiful views. The menu features locally sourced seafood and produce, and the wine list is extensive.

fields.name: Breakfast at Croissants de France
fields.itinerary_description: Start your day with a delicious French breakfast at Croissants de France. Try the croissants or the quiche Lorraine!

fields.name: Visit the Butterfly and Nature Conservatory
fields.itinerary_description: Explore the beautiful world of butterflies and birds at the Butterfly and Nature Conservatory. Walk through the glass-enclosed habitat and see more than 50 species of butterflies and birds from around the world.

fields.name: Lunch at Garbo's Grill
fields.itinerary_description: Grab lunch at Garbo's Grill, a popular food truck in Key West. Try the fish tacos or the Yum Yum shrimp!

fields.name: Kayak in the Mangroves
fields.itinerary_description: Explore the beautiful mangrove ecosystem of Key West by kayak. Take a guided tour and see the diverse wildlife that call the mangroves home.

fields.name: Happy Hour at Alonzo's Oyster Bar
fields.itinerary_description: Enjoy happy hour at Alonzo's Oyster Bar, located in the Historic Seaport area of Key West. Try the oysters or the conch ceviche!

fields.name: Dinner at Latitude's
fields.itinerary_description: Enjoy a delicious dinner at Latitude's in Key West, FL. This restaurant offers fresh seafood and beautiful waterfront views.

fields.name: Breakfast at The Little Diner
fields.itinerary_description: Start your day with a delicious breakfast at The Little Diner, a cozy and popular breakfast spot in Vail. Try their famous biscuits and gravy or one of their many omelet options!

fields.name: Skiing at Vail Mountain
fields.itinerary_description: Hit the slopes at Vail Mountain, one of the largest ski resorts in North America with over 5,000 acres of skiable terrain. Enjoy the beautiful scenery and the variety of runs suitable for all levels.

fields.name: Apres-Ski at The Red Lion
fields.itinerary_description: After a long day of skiing, head to The Red Lion, a popular apres-ski spot in Vail. Enjoy live music, a casual atmosphere, and a wide selection of drinks and pub food.

fields.name: Dinner at Sweet Basil
fields.itinerary_description: Indulge in a fine dining experience at Sweet Basil, known for its contemporary American cuisine and extensive wine list. Be sure to make a reservation in advance!

fields.name: Snowshoeing in White River National Forest
fields.itinerary_description: Experience the beauty of Colorado's winter landscape with a guided snowshoe tour through White River National Forest. Enjoy stunning views and fresh mountain air while learning about the local ecosystem.

fields.name: Lunch at La Cantina
fields.itinerary_description: Head to La Cantina for some delicious Mexican food and drinks. This cozy spot serves up tasty tacos, burritos, and more, as well as a wide variety of tequila and margarita options.

fields.name: Snowmobiling in Vail Pass
fields.itinerary_description: Experience the thrill of snowmobiling through the stunning Vail Pass backcountry. Take in the breathtaking views while zooming through the snow on a guided tour.

fields.name: Hot Springs Soak at Glenwood Springs
fields.itinerary_description: Relax and unwind at the Glenwood Hot Springs, the world's largest hot springs pool. Soak in the mineral-rich waters while taking in the beautiful mountain views.

fields.name: Breakfast at The Little Diner Too
fields.itinerary_description: Start your day with a delicious breakfast at The Little Diner Too, the sister location of The Little Diner. Try their famous pancakes or one of their many breakfast burrito options!

fields.name: Skiing at Beaver Creek
fields.itinerary_description: Spend the day skiing at Beaver Creek, a world-class ski resort located just 15 minutes from Vail. Enjoy the variety of runs and beautiful mountain scenery.

fields.name: Late Lunch at Moe's Original BBQ
fields.itinerary_description: Head to Moe's Original BBQ for some delicious southern-style barbecue. This casual spot serves up tasty pulled pork, brisket, and more.

fields.name: Ice Skating at Dobson Ice Arena
fields.itinerary_description: Go ice skating at Dobson Ice Arena, located in the heart of Vail. Enjoy skating on the outdoor rink while taking in the beautiful mountain views.

fields.name: Dinner at Mountain Standard
fields.itinerary_description: Indulge in a fine dining experience at Mountain Standard, known for its innovative and seasonal cuisine. Be sure to make a reservation in advance!

fields.name: Breakfast at Clint's Bakery and Coffee House
fields.itinerary_description: Start your day with delicious baked goods and coffee at Clint's Bakery and Coffee House. This cozy bakery offers a variety of sweet and savory pastries, bagels, and breakfast sandwiches.

fields.name: Snowboarding at Breckenridge Ski Resort
fields.itinerary_description: Hit the slopes at Breckenridge Ski Resort, one of the top ski destinations in North America. With 2,908 acres of skiable terrain, 34 lifts, and 187 trails, there's something for everyone.

fields.name: Happy Hour at The Breckenridge Brewery
fields.itinerary_description: After a day on the slopes, relax with some locally brewed beer and pub fare at The Breckenridge Brewery. This popular spot offers a range of craft beers, cocktails, and delicious bites.

fields.name: Spa Day at the Arrabelle
fields.itinerary_description: Relax and rejuvenate with a spa day at the Arrabelle at Vail Square. Choose from a variety of treatments, including massages, facials, and body wraps, and enjoy the luxurious atmosphere of the spa.

fields.name: Travel to Paris
fields.itinerary_description: Our flight number is DL374, and it boards 40 minutes prior to departure.

fields.name: Arrive in Paris
fields.itinerary_description: Arrive in Paris and head to hotel to catch some rest.  Hotel is Four Seasons Hotel George V Paris

fields.name: Eiffel Tower
fields.itinerary_description: Visit the iconic Eiffel Tower, take in the views from the observation deck, and enjoy a picnic lunch on the Champ de Mars.

fields.name: Louvre Museum
fields.itinerary_description: Explore the world-renowned Louvre Museum and see some of its most famous works of art, including the Mona Lisa.

fields.name: Seine River Cruise
fields.itinerary_description: Relax on a scenic Seine River Cruise and enjoy stunning views of Paris from the water.

fields.name: Montmartre
fields.itinerary_description: Visit the charming neighborhood of Montmartre, take in the view of the city from the Basilique du Sacré-Cœur, and enjoy some crepes at a local cafe.

fields.name: Palace of Versailles
fields.itinerary_description: Take a day trip to the Palace of Versailles and explore its opulent halls, gardens, and fountains.

fields.name: Disneyland Paris
fields.itinerary_description: Experience the magic of Disneyland Paris! Ride Space Mountain, Big Thunder Mountain Railroad, and Pirates of the Caribbean. Take pictures with your favorite Disney characters and enjoy the parades and shows. Grab lunch at Chez Remy or Captain Jack's Restaurant.

fields.name: Breakfast at Hotel
fields.itinerary_description: Indulge in a delicious breakfast at hotel. Enjoy a variety of French pastries, fresh fruit, and other delectable dishes.

fields.name: Get ready for Max & Julie's Wedding
fields.itinerary_description: Get ready in the room.  Wearing the green dress and planning to curl hair.

fields.name: Max & Julie's Wedding
fields.itinerary_description: Get ready in the room.  Wearing the green dress and planning to curl hair.

fields.name: Attending Max & Julie's Wedding
fields.itinerary_description: Attend Max and Julie's wedding at the Shangri-La Hotel in Paris. Enjoy the ceremony, reception, and dancing with friends and family.

fields.name: Historic Paris
fields.itinerary_description: Explore the historic heart of Paris and see some of its most iconic landmarks, including Notre-Dame, Sainte-Chapelle, and the Panthéon.

fields.name: Shopping and Dining
fields.itinerary_description: Spend the afternoon shopping and dining in the trendy Marais neighborhood. Visit independent boutiques and sample local cuisine at cafes and restaurants.

fields.name: Evening in Montparnasse
fields.itinerary_description: Enjoy an evening in the Montparnasse neighborhood. Take in the view from the top of the Tour Montparnasse, then enjoy dinner and drinks at a local brasserie.

fields.name: Fly back to Nashville
fields.itinerary_description: Flight is DL2024
